snippet.textDisplay: VAR is just a clusterf**k.   Cancelled my Sky sports as the Premier League has become just like Wrestling from the 80s - all contrived entertainment with no passion.    How the hell they can order a penalty to be retaken when the man city player is the furthers encroacher - just sums up the state of the game.   It wouldn't even be so bad if they were consistent, but one week a keeper will get away with both feet off the line on a penalty, the next week we get a different VAR opinion.   Just mindless acceptance of technology that is giving no better results than we had before.  At least the City keeper got sent off, most weeks that would have been a booking by the ref and no intervention by VAR.

snippet.textDisplay:
All the pundits across all platforms talking only of man city failures,not a word hardly of what wolves had done,sure they were against 10 men,but let's not forget they shocked everyone last time beating man city in the reverse of this game a few months ago.
And the commentator saying something along the lines of have wolves won the title for Liverpool is a total farce,lfc didn't rely on this or any other result of our rivals,we have gone and done it ourselves,so don't belittle that,we destroyed Leicester who are on fire 4_0,and all we have done prior.
So respect lfc pls, if it was city who did as lfc did to their next best rival sky etc would laud pep as the genius etc,but lfc are being gifted the pl it seems lol.
Also let's pay homage to wolves boss Nuno he was first to show the "smaller clubs" how to play the top team's,and he's brought a second tier club to the top table,and rather than be overwhelmed by it they've played some brilliant football,and stuck with their attacking philosophy as if fearless no matter the opposition,but actually being effective enough to defend quite well also,I respect how they carry themselves,and their manager too.
